<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="97" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,885,1038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,917,941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1900" box="[291,569,919,942]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Macromonycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolica">
<emphasis box="[291,569,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Macromonycha anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[852,949,918,942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
. It is quite well characterized by its oval body shape distinctly widened around midlength, moderately elevated elytral structures, and uniformly rusty-yellow dorsum in combination with yellow venter and black head. For a detailed redescription see 
<bibRefCitation author="BOROWIEC L." box="[619,805,1014,1038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" pagination="81 - 86" refId="ref4751" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2001: Redescription of Macromonycha anatolica (Weise, 1900) (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 12: 81 - 86." type="journal article" year="2001">BOROWIEC (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
